<h1 tal:replace="structure here/manage_page_header">Header</h1>

<h2 tal:define="manage_tabs_message options/manage_tabs_message | nothing"
    tal:replace="structure here/manage_tabs">Tabs</h2>

<h4><a href="../manage_services">Silva Services</a></h4>

<h2>
  Manage Simple MemberService
</h2>

<form action="." method="post" class="form-text">

<table width="500">
  <tr>
    <td valign="top" width="300">
      <div class="form-label">Allow membership requests on this site:</div>
      <div class="form-element">
        <input type="radio" name="allow_authentication_requests" value="0" tal:attributes="checked python: test(here.allow_authentication_requests(), '', 'CHECKED')" />No<br />
        <input type="radio" name="allow_authentication_requests" value="1" tal:attributes="checked python: test(here.allow_authentication_requests(), 'CHECKED', '')" />Yes<br />
      </div>
    </td>
    <td class="form-text" valign="top">
      When set to 'Yes', a user will be presented a link to request roles on an object if he/she fails to authenticate. The requests will be e-mailed to the (nearest) ChiefEditor(s), who can then allow or deny the role to that user in the access tab of the object.
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign="top" width="300">
      <div class="form-label">Use direct lookup:</div>
      <div class="form-element">
        <input type="radio" name="use_direct_lookup" value="0" tal:attributes="checked python: test(here.use_direct_lookup(), '', 'CHECKED')" />No<br />
        <input type="radio" name="use_direct_lookup" value="1" tal:attributes="checked python: test(here.use_direct_lookup(), 'CHECKED', '')" />Yes<br />
      </div>
    </td>
    <td class="form-text" valign="top">
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2" valign="top">
      <input type="submit" name="manage_editServiceSettings:method" value="Change Settings" class="form-element" />
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
</form>

